ns of your penmanship, he would study the strokes and the linkage, and then turn out your individual padograph. The resulting script copied exactly the average 'tone' of your handwriting while the minor variations of each character were taken care of by the several keys serving each letter. Punctuation marks were carefully diversified within the limits of this or that individual manner, and such details as spacing and what experts call 'clines' were so rendered as to mask mechanical regularity. 